# Project Architecture: Web Ad Automation Dashboard

This document provides a comprehensive overview of your project's architecture, outlining how the different pieces of your web automation dashboard connect and function.

## High-Level Architecture Overview

Your project is an end-to-end web automation platform designed to programmatically navigate to websites, detect advertisements, overlay them with your own local creative assets (images), and capture screenshots of the modified pages. 

The system consists of three main tiers:
1. **Frontend (Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS)**: A responsive dashboard UI to interact with the backend API, start automation tasks, and view historical screenshots.
2. **Backend API (FastAPI)**: A fast, asynchronous Python API that orchestrates the workflow between the frontend, database, and browser engine.
3. **Automation Engine (Playwright)**: An asynchronous headless browser that injects scripts to manipulate DOM elements (finding ads, removing popups) and takes snapshots.
4. **Database (PostgreSQL)**: Stores the historical results of the automation (success/failure, match counts, image paths).

